Reasoning: The paper deals with Chu spaces, which are a mathematical structure used in linear logic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the existence of colimits and the characterization of monomorphisms, which are topics related to category theory and algebraic structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also touches on the topic of recursion, which is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
